  <!-- navigation object : Breadcrumbs --><div id="breadcrumb">You are here: <a href="/">Home</a> > <a href="/media/">Media</a> > <a href="/media/covid-19-information/">COVID-19 - Information</a> > COVID-19 - Press Statements</div>
  <br /><h1>Press Release</h1>

<h2>TUF agrees additional layer of protection for construction workers with CIF</h2>
<p>Date Released: 21 May 2020</p>

<p>The Trade Union Federation, comprising Ireland's largest construction unions, SIPTU, BATU and Connect have signed a landmark agreement with the Construction Industry Federation (CIF) to ensure the safety of workers across the industry.</p>

<p><p><strong></strong>The additional and industry specific measures to deal with the threat of Covid-19 include a monitoring system, improved access to sites for union representatives, alternative work patterns and temperature testing of workers.</p>
<p>According to SIPTU Construction Sector Organiser, John Regan, the agreement provides for additional safety and health protection measures to those already agreed between employers and trade unions over recent weeks.</p>
<p>&ldquo;These measures are based on the principle of &lsquo;prevention first&rsquo;, the speedy correction of non-compliance and the closure of sites if the safety of workers is not ensured. If it cannot be done safely, it should not be done at all,&rdquo; he said.&nbsp;</p>
<p>The Assistant General Secretary of Connect, Brian Nolan said: &ldquo;Construction workers and their families need the assurances about their safety contained in this agreement as they return to work. The issue should not be used as a political football.&rdquo;</p>
<p>The General Secretary of BATU, Brendan O&rsquo;Sullivan said: &ldquo;This agreement gives unionised workers a way to highlight unsafe practices without fear of victimisation. Construction workers need to play a role on each site as safety representatives and if they are not yet union members, they should join today.&rdquo;</p>
<p>The Agreement between the TUF and the CIF was signed today at the Connect offices in Dublin.</p>
<p><a href="https://youtu.be/7g-zcYDm1zE">View the video</a></p></p>

